parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering assist can cause the steering wheel to become difficult to turn or stuck, making it hard to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The power steering assist fault message appears on the instrument cluster
the steering wheel feels soft or spongy
the steering wheel sticks to the floor
the steering wheel does not return to its normal position
the steering wheel has a delayed return to its normal position
the steering wheel has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Intermittent Electrical Failure of Advance Trak Traction Control System
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent failure of the Advance Trak traction control system can cause the vehicle to unexpectedly pull to the left or right while accelerating, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The vehicle pulls to the left or right while accelerating
the vehicle makes an abnormal moan/groan sound
the traction control light illuminates on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Steering Gear Failure in EPAS Steering System
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering gear in the EPAS steering system can cause the power steering to fail, making it difficult to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: the steering wheel feels stiff or difficult to turn
the steering wheel jerks or vibrates
a loud noise is heard from the steering system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the water pump can cause the engine to overheat, leading to engine failure, loss of power, and potentially causing accidents or stranding the driver.
symptoms: The coolant temperature warning light comes on

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the turbocharger can cause the engine to lose power, leading to accidents or stranding the driver. It can also cause excessive smoke to come from the exhaust pipes.
symptoms: black smoke exits from the exhaust pipes
and the vehicle may stall or shut down.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or stranding the driver. It can also cause loss of power steering and power brakes, making it difficult to control the vehicle.
symptoms: and the power steering and power brakes may fail.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the piston rings can cause the engine to lose compression, leading to engine failure and potentially causing accidents or stranding the driver.
symptoms: white smoke exits from the exhaust pipes
and the engine may stall or shut down.
